               <p>THOMAS WHITE. I am a <rs id="t18300218-43-viclabel231" type="occupation">rope-maker's labourer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300218-43-victim358 t18300218-43-viclabel231"></join>, and live at <placeName id="t18300218-43-crimeloc232">Limehouse</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18300218-43-crimeloc232" type="placeName" value="Limehouse"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18300218-43-crimeloc232" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300218-43-off229 t18300218-43-crimeloc232"></join>. On the 26th of January I let the prisoner sleep with me, as I had known him some time before; I got up first the next morning, went to my labour, and left the articles safe in my trunk in my room, it was locked - I came home at three o'clock, found the trunk broken open, and the handkerchief, coat, trousers, and two half-crowns were gone; I took the prisoner on the 28th - he said, "Come along with me, and I will tell you all about it;" I was certain he was the man, and had him taken.</p>
